<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Frequently Asked Questions</title>

    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/twitter-bootstrap/5.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.6.0/jquery.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles/faq.css">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="./images/brand-icon/logo-big.png">
</head>

<body>
    <nav>
        <a href="/index">Home</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact Us</a>
    </nav>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
        <div class="faq-wrapper">
            <div class="header">
                <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-inner">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        What is Travel Buddy and how does it work?
                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4>Travel Buddy is a website that helps college students find travel mates for the same or
                            nearby destinations on the same dates and time. Users can post their travel details and
                            other interested users can approach them through the website or contact details provided.
                        </h4></div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        Is Travel Buddy safe to use?
                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4> Yes, Travel Buddy takes the safety and security of its users seriously. All users must
                            create an account and verify their email address before posting or responding to travel
                            requests. Users can also view other users' profiles and reviews before deciding to travel
                            with them.
                        </h4></div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        How much does it cost to use Travel Buddy?
                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4>Travel Buddy is completely free to use! There are no hidden fees or charges for posting or
                            responding to travel requests.
                        </h4></div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        Can I use Travel Buddy to find travel mates for international trips?
                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4>Yes, Travel Buddy can be used to find travel mates for both domestic and international
                            trips. Just be sure to check any travel restrictions or visa requirements before making
                            plans with your travel mate.
                        </h4></div>
                    <hr>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>
                            What if I can't find a suitable travel mate on Travel Buddy?
                            <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                        </h3>
                        <div class="faq-body">
                            <h4>If you can't find a suitable travel mate on Travel Buddy, you can always try posting
                                your request on social media or travel forums. You can also consider traveling solo or
                                joining a group tour.
                            </h4></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="container">

        <div class="faq-wrapper">
            <div class="header">

            </div>
            <div class="faq-inner">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        How do I know if my travel mate is reliable?
                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4> Before traveling with a potential travel mate, you can view their profile and any reviews
                            or ratings from other users. You can also message or talk to them to get to know them better
                            before making plans.
                        </h4></div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        What if my travel plans change after finding a travel mate on Travel Buddy?
                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4>If your travel plans change, be sure to communicate with your travel mate as soon as
                            possible to avoid any confusion or inconvenience. You can also update your travel request on
                            Travel Buddy to reflect any changes.</div>
                    </h4> </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        Can I use Travel Buddy to find travel mates for non-college related trips?
                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4> While Travel Buddy is primarily designed for college students, anyone can use the website
                            to find travel mates for any type of trip. Just keep in mind that most users will be college
                            students looking for budget-friendly travel options.</div>
                    </h4></div>
                <hr>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        What if I have more questions about Travel Buddy?

                        <span class="faq-plus">&plus;</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-body">
                        <h4> If you have any additional questions or concerns about using Travel Buddy, you can contact
                            the website's customer support team or check out the FAQ page for more information.</div>
                    </h4>
                    <hr>
                    <div class="faq-item">

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <script type="text/javascript">
        $(".faq-plus").on('click', function () {
            $(this).parent().parent().find('.faq-body').slideToggle();
        });
    </script>
</body>

</html>